cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper deals with building a neural model for recommendation systems that can handle both short-term and long-term dependencies in user behavior. This involves analyzing large datasets of user sequences and proposing a Multi-temporal-range Mixture Model (M3) that combines different models with different temporal ranges based on contextual information. This work involves machine learning and natural language processing techniques, which are typically covered in the arXiv sub-categories of cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, and cs.SI.
